args:
Leonidas shows the prince a letter from a man
named Gatov, who wishes to guide the prince
to the Faerie Kingdom. He then orders him to
Grams in North Grastaea to meet with the man.
The prince assents, and Chelle ends up
accompanying him on the journey.
Hold still, Ciella!\nWe must treat your wounds!
Stay your pity! I'd sooner perish and\ncrumble into dust than accept it!
Begone from here. If fleeing goes against\nyour sense of aesthetics—such as they\nare—then I shall give you pretext.

Return to this ＂Nedrick＂ and tell him thus:
Retribution for casting Alberia into chaos
and making mockery of my brother comes
sure and swift as the morrow's sun.
Two siblings cut from the same cloth.\nYou people truly are hopeless.
Why have you changed so much, Ciella?
No time for navel-gazing, folks!\nWe got a military force comin' our way!
That standard they're flying... It's Chelle!
You've come at last, Chelle. Good.\nNow let us all make for the Halidom;\nthe time has come for a discussion.

What a shame I wasn't here in time to see
you dealing with that ineffable miscreant
spreading false rumors OR the purification
of that ghastly void dragon.
Finishing everything before I even arrive?\nHonestly! The two of you clearly have\nno idea of how to entertain a lady.
If anyone knew exactly what would be\nsettled and when, Chelle, it is you.\nYou came precisely when you wished to.

In any event, I have not the time to waste
on your theatrics. This discussion begins
now, and all those not of the royal family
must depart at once.
Actually, Brother, I'd like them to stay.\nThey're in this with me.
Such is your way, is it? Very well.
Thank you. Now, what is it that you\nwant to talk to us about?
What do you know of it?
Do not misunderstand: I had no direct\nknowledge of your secret, nor did I ever\nhear anything from our late father.
That historical book is not spurious.\nIt was, without a doubt, stolen from the\npossession of the royal family.
Highly likely to be true, yes. I'm sorry,\nmy brother, but you mostlike do not bear\nthe blood of our father.
That's... Wow. That's hard to hear.
Keep your head until I am finished, I beg.\nI turn now to the covenant referenced\nin the document.
Neither seal nor signature was forged.\nThere can be no doubt it was our father\nwho made the agreement.
As the signature states, the man who\nexchanged a child with our father in that\nsecret agreement was named Finlorda.

This Finlorda rules a land in northern
Grastaea that once had a relationship
with Alberia. Specifically, he is the king
of the Faerie Kingdom.
Are you saying {player_name}\nwas born in this Faerie Kingdom?
Yo, Notte! Give us the details here!\nWhat's this Faerie Kingdom like?
Dude, I have no freakin' idea. I didn't even\nknow it EXISTED until like six seconds ago.
I mean, I guess I'd heard about a place in\nNorth Grastaea where faeries lived, but...
Yeah, I dunno. I mean, I've lived here\nin Alberia for my entire life.
But my brother is clearly no faerie,\nno matter where he may hail from.
I have yet to ascertain any firm facts\non your true origins.
However, a man in North Grastaea may\nhold the key—I received this missive\nfrom him some days prior.

＂When news of Aurelius's death reached
me, I took pen in hand whilst reminiscing
upon the days of yore in which we
deepened our bonds of friendship.＂
＂I suspect the time is nigh for me to fulfill\nthe duty entrusted to me by him.＂
＂The duty to guide {player_name}\nto the Faerie Kingdom in North Grastaea.＂
＂To that end, I request you inform the lad\nto make for the Holy City of Grams.＂
＂As his elder brother, please facilitate his\nsafe departure from Alberia.＂
...It's signed, ＂Gatov, Captain of Grams's\n12th Division Watch.＂
Do you know this Grams, dear brother?
It is the capital of North Grastaea;\na city ruled by the Ilian Church.
When he was alive, Father instructed me\nto make for Grams should he ever meet\nwith his demise.
It seems that, too, is evidence he was\nrelying upon this man Gatov.
Do you know this Gatov person?

He had a close relationship with our father
stretching back many years. But though
he has visited the royal castle several
times, I know little by way of specifics.
This is the end of what I have to tell you.
But by rights as your elder brother,\nI now issue this command to you:
Leave Alberia at once, make for Grams,\nand find our father's friend Gatov.
But what about the Halidom?!\nIn fact, what about ALBERIA?!\nWho will protect them if I'm gone?!

Everything that's happened recently has
made me face a very unpleasant fact:
I pursued the Other and Zethia at the
expense of my own people.
We walk a razor's edge with them now,\nand I won't leave with things in such\na precarious balance!
As I said when I stood down the people,\nI govern Alberia.

The present turmoil may have subsided,
but those who oppose our family will soon
make use of the rumors concerning you
once again.
Your wish to aid Alberia is noble indeed,\nbut your remaining here could well serve\nto undermine her instead of helping.
What's more, reports indicate that this\nNedrick man is headed north with Zethia.

My information is ALWAYS sound. And so,
is it not preferable for us to observe their
movements up close and perhaps have our
dear sister returned to us unharmed?
Well, if Zethia will be in the north...
I cannot guess at present as to what\nyour true origins may be.
But no matter who you might be, you are\nmy brother—and the man who bested me.

Seek the wider world. Broaden your
horizons. See all that you must until you
are satisfied with the answer to the 
question of who, exactly, you are.
Thank you, Leonidas. Your words feel like\nthey've lifted a weight off my spirits.
A little travel ain't a bad idea, actually.
Heck yeah! Let's hit North Grastaea!
Whatever is to come, we are with you.
I shall be ever at your side,\nno matter what trials await.
Let's head to the north, Brother!\nLet's find the true you!
I'm still not certain this is the right path,\nbut for the time being, I'll head to Grams.
But I worry that my siblings are going to\nface a mountain of trouble while I'm gone.
Leonidas? Chelle? Please look after\nNew Alberia, her soldiers, and her people.
Tsk tsk tsk! You don't really expect me to\nsit around with this grump and play house\nwhile you traipse about the world, do you?
Why, it's more worry than I could stand,\nthinking of my beloved little brother off\non this big journey all alone.
You can't really expect me to sit still\nand wait for your return, mmm?
Furthermore, I've always found Alberia\nto be rather stifling for a learned\nwoman such as myself.
For me, dear brother, the only suitable\nstage is the whole wide world!
I'm sorry, are you saying that you're\ngoing to come with us?
Be glad in your hearts! With me as your\ncounsel, you've naught to fear—no matter\nhow burdensome your journey may be.
This is also my request, Brother; I feel that\nChelle can be of great assistance to you.
I can't deny that it would be reassuring to\nhave her along, but are you going to be\nall right here all on your own?
I am more than enough to see to Alberia's\naffairs. When you return, I suspect all\nthe realm's problems will be well sorted.
Eee hee hee! Such stirring words indeed!\nLet us see just what the eldest son of the\nAlberian royal family can do.
Now that we've come to our conclusion,\nI will be returning briefly to Chanzelia that\nI might prepare for our expedition.
I will contact you when my preparations\nare complete. Until then, farewell.
And I return to Valkaheim. Get your affairs\nin order and your preparations made soon.
Thank you both for being the guiding lights\nin my life. I won't let you down.
Okay, everyone! Let's get together and\ndiscuss what we need to do in order to\nleave the Halidom!
